205 int32_t MmwDemo_gen_twiddle_fft32x32_fast(int32_t *w, int32_t n, double scale)
206  {
207  int32_t i, j, k;
208  int32_t log2n = 30 - _norm(n); //Note n is always power of 2
209  int32_t step = 1024 >> log2n;
210  int32_t step6 = 3 * step;
211  int32_t step4 = 2 * step;
212  int32_t step2 = 1 * step;
213  int32_t ind, indLsb, indMsb;
214  int64_t * restrict table = (int64_t *) twiddleTableCommon;
215  int64_t * restrict wd = (int64_t *) w;
216  int32_t xRe;
217  int32_t xIm;
218 
219  for (j = 1, k = 0; j < n >> 2; j = j << 2) {
220  for (i =0; i < n >> 2; i += j) {
221  ind = step2 * (i);
222  indLsb = ind & 0xFF;
223  indMsb = (ind >> 8) & 0x3;
224  xRe = _hill(table[indLsb]);
225  xIm = _loll(table[indLsb]);
226  if (indMsb == 0)
227  {
228  wd[k + 0] = _itoll(xRe, xIm);
229  }
230  if (indMsb == 1)
231  {
232  wd[k + 0] = _itoll(-xIm, xRe);
233  }
234  if (indMsb == 2)
235  {
236  wd[k + 0] = _itoll(-xRe, -xIm);
237  }
238 
239  ind = step4 * (i);
240  indLsb = ind & 0xFF;
241  indMsb = (ind >> 8) & 0x3;
242  xRe = _hill(table[indLsb]);
243  xIm = _loll(table[indLsb]);
244  if (indMsb == 0)
245  {
246  wd[k + 1] = _itoll(xRe, xIm);
247  }
248  if (indMsb == 1)
249  {
250  wd[k + 1] = _itoll(-xIm, xRe);
251  }
252  if (indMsb == 2)
253  {
254  wd[k + 1] = _itoll(-xRe, -xIm);
255  }
256 
257  ind = step6 * (i);
258  indLsb = ind & 0xFF;
259  indMsb = (ind >> 8) & 0x3;
260  xRe = _hill(table[indLsb]);
261  xIm = _loll(table[indLsb]);
262  if (indMsb == 0)
263  {
264  wd[k + 2] = _itoll(xRe, xIm);
265  }
266  if (indMsb == 1)
267  {
268  wd[k + 2] = _itoll(-xIm, xRe);
269  }

271  {
272  wd[k + 2] = _itoll(-xRe, -xIm);
273  }
274 
275  k += 3;
276  }
277  }

545 int32_t MmwDemo_getDopplerLine(MmwDemo_1D_DopplerLines_t * ths)
546 {
547  uint32_t index = ths->currentIndex;
548  uint32_t word = index >> 5;
549  uint32_t bit = index & 31;
550 
551  while (((ths->dopplerLineMask[word] >> bit) & 0x1) == 0)
552  {
553  index++;
554  bit++;
555  if (bit == 32)
556  {
557  word++;
558  bit = 0;
559  if (word >= ths->dopplerLineMaskLen)
560  {
561  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
562  }
563  }
564  }
565  ths->currentIndex = index + 1;
566  return index;
567 }

606 void MmwDemo_XYcalc (MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *obj,
607  uint32_t objIndex,
608  uint16_t azimIdx,
609  float maxVal)
610 {
611  int32_t sMaxIdx;
612  float temp;
613  float Wx;
614  float range;
615  float x, y;
616  uint32_t xyzOutputQFormat = obj->xyzOutputQFormat;
617 #define ONE_QFORMAT (1 << xyzOutputQFormat)
618  float rangeResolution = obj->rangeResolution;
619 
620 
621  uint32_t numAngleBins = obj->numAngleBins;
622  uint32_t numDopplerBins = obj->numDopplerBins;
623  uint32_t numRangeBins = obj->numRangeBins;
624 
625 
626  obj->detObj2dAzimIdx[objIndex] = azimIdx;
627 
628  /* Save square root of maximum peak to object peak value scaling */
629  temp = divsp(maxVal, (numRangeBins * numAngleBins * numDopplerBins));
630  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].peakVal = (uint16_t)sqrtsp(temp);
631 
632  /* Calculate X and Y coordinates in meters in Q format */
633 #ifdef MMW_ENABLE_NEGATIVE_FREQ_SLOPE
634  if (rangeResolution > 0)
635  {
636  range = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx * rangeResolution;
637  }
638  else
639  {
640  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx = (uint16_t) ((int32_t) obj->numRangeBins - (int32_t) obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx);
641  range = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx * -rangeResolution;
642  }
643 #else
644  range = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx * rangeResolution;
645 #endif
646 
647  /* Compensate for range bias */
648  range -= obj->cliCommonCfg->compRxChanCfg.rangeBias;
649  if (range < 0)
650  {
651  range = 0;
652  }
653 
654  if(azimIdx > (numAngleBins/2 -1))
655  {
656  sMaxIdx = azimIdx - numAngleBins;
657  }
658  else
659  {
660  sMaxIdx = azimIdx;
661  }
662 
663  Wx = 2 * (float) sMaxIdx / numAngleBins;
664  x = range * Wx;
665 
666  /* y = sqrt(range^2 - x^2) */
667  temp = range*range -x*x ;
668  if (temp > 0)
669  {
670  y = sqrtsp(temp);
671  }
672  else
673  {
674  y = 0;
675  }
676 
677  /* Convert to Q format */
678  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].x = (int16_t) ROUND(x * ONE_QFORMAT);
679  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].y = (int16_t) ROUND(y * ONE_QFORMAT);
680  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].z = 0;
681 }

700 void MmwDemo_XYestimation(MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *obj,
701  uint32_t objIndex)
702 {
703  uint32_t i;
704  float *azimuthMagSqr = obj->azimuthMagSqr;
705  uint32_t numAngleBins = obj->numAngleBins;
706  uint32_t numSearchBins;
707 
708  uint32_t azimIdx = 0;
709  float maxVal = 0;
710 
711  if(obj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled && (obj->numVirtualAntAzim > obj->numRxAntennas))
712  {
713  numSearchBins = numAngleBins * 2;
714  }
715  else
716  {
717  numSearchBins = numAngleBins;
718  }
719  /* Find peak position - search in original and flipped output */
720  for (i = 0; i < numSearchBins ; i++)
721  {
722  if (azimuthMagSqr[i] > maxVal)
723  {
724  azimIdx = i;
725  maxVal = azimuthMagSqr[i];
726  }
727  }
728  if(obj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled && (obj->numVirtualAntAzim > obj->numRxAntennas))
729  {
730  if(azimIdx >= numAngleBins)
731  {
732  /* Velocity aliased: |velocity| > Vmax */
733  /* Correct peak index: */
734  azimIdx -= numAngleBins;
735  /* Correct velocity */
736  if (obj->detObj2D[objIndex].dopplerIdx < 0)
737  {
738  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].dopplerIdx += (int16_t) obj->numDopplerBins;
739  }
740  else
741  {
742  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].dopplerIdx -= (int16_t) obj->numDopplerBins;
743  }
744  }
745  }
746 
747  MmwDemo_XYcalc (obj,
748  objIndex,
749  azimIdx,
750  maxVal);
751 
752  /* Check for second peak */
753  if (obj->cliCfg->multiObjBeamFormingCfg.enabled && (!obj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled))
754  {
755  uint32_t leftSearchIdx;
756  uint32_t rightSearchIdx;
757  uint32_t secondSearchLen;
758  uint32_t iModAzimLen;
759  float maxVal2;
760  int32_t k;
761 
762  /* Find right edge of the first peak */
763  i = azimIdx;
764  leftSearchIdx = (i + 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
765  k = numAngleBins;
766  while ((azimuthMagSqr[i] >= azimuthMagSqr[leftSearchIdx]) && (k > 0))
767  {
768  i = (i + 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
769  leftSearchIdx = (leftSearchIdx + 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
770  k--;
771  }
772 
773  /* Find left edge of the first peak */
774  i = azimIdx;
775  rightSearchIdx = (i - 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
776  k = numAngleBins;
777  while ((azimuthMagSqr[i] >= azimuthMagSqr[rightSearchIdx]) && (k > 0))
778  {
779  i = (i - 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
780  rightSearchIdx = (rightSearchIdx - 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
781  k--;
782  }
783 
784  secondSearchLen = ((rightSearchIdx - leftSearchIdx) & (numAngleBins-1)) + 1;
785  /* Find second peak */
786  maxVal2 = azimuthMagSqr[leftSearchIdx];
787  azimIdx = leftSearchIdx;
788  for (i = leftSearchIdx; i < (leftSearchIdx + secondSearchLen); i++)
789  {
790  iModAzimLen = i & (numAngleBins-1);
791  if (azimuthMagSqr[iModAzimLen] > maxVal2)
792  {
793  azimIdx = iModAzimLen;
794  maxVal2 = azimuthMagSqr[iModAzimLen];
795  }
796  }
797 
798  /* Is second peak greater than threshold? */
799  if (maxVal2 > (maxVal * obj->cliCfg->multiObjBeamFormingCfg.multiPeakThrsScal) && (obj->numDetObj < MMW_MAX_OBJ_OUT))
800  {
801  /* Second peak detected! Add it to the end of the list */
802  obj->detObj2D[obj->numDetObj].dopplerIdx = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].dopplerIdx;
803  obj->detObj2D[obj->numDetObj].rangeIdx = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx;
804  objIndex = obj->numDetObj;
805  obj->numDetObj++;
806 
807  MmwDemo_XYcalc (obj,
808  objIndex,
809  azimIdx,
810  maxVal2);
811  }
812  }
813 }

1204 void MmwDemo_EDMA_CQTransferCompletionCallbackFxn(uintptr_t arg,
1205  uint8_t transferCompletionCode)
1206 {
1207  MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *obj = (MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *)arg;
1208  uint8_t chirpIdx;
1209 
1210  switch (transferCompletionCode)
1211  {
1212  /* Validate numSlices from data buffer for every chirp.
1213  Note1: If the configured number of slices covers more time period than the sampling time,
1214  the actual reported number of slices maybe smaller.
1215 
1216  Note 2: If there are extensive CQ data processing,
1217  then the processing code should be moved to a task
1218  */
1219 
1220  case MMW_EDMA_CH_SIGIMG_MON:
1221  obj->datapathCQ.sigImgEdmaCnt++;
1222  for(chirpIdx = 0; chirpIdx < obj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent; chirpIdx++)
1223  {
1224  uint8_t *sigImgData = obj->datapathCQ.sigImgData;
1225 
1226  if(sigImgData[chirpIdx * obj->datapathCQ.sigImgMonDataSizePerChirp] > obj->datapathCQ.sigImgMonCfg->numSlices)
1227  {
1228  obj->datapathCQ.sigImgErrCnt++;
1229  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
1230  }
1231  }
1232  break;
1233 
1234  case MMW_EDMA_CH_RX_SATURATION_MON:
1235  obj->datapathCQ.rxSatEdmaCnt++;
1236  for(chirpIdx = 0; chirpIdx < obj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent; chirpIdx++)
1237  {
1238  uint8_t *rxSatData = obj->datapathCQ.rxSatData;
1239  if(rxSatData[chirpIdx * obj->datapathCQ.satMonDataSizePerChirp] > obj->datapathCQ.rxSatMonCfg->numSlices)
1240  {
1241  obj->datapathCQ.rxSatErrCnt++;
1242  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
1243  }
1244  }
1245  break;

1710 uint32_t MmwDemo_cfarPeakGrouping(
1711  MmwDemo_detectedObj* objOut,
1712  MmwDemo_objRaw_t * objRaw,
1713  uint32_t numDetectedObjects,
1714  uint16_t* detMatrix,
1715  uint32_t numDopplerBins,
1716  uint32_t maxRangeIdx,
1717  uint32_t minRangeIdx,
1718  uint32_t groupInDopplerDirection,
1719  uint32_t groupInRangeDirection)
1720 {
1721  int32_t i, j;
1722  int32_t rowStart, rowEnd;
1723  uint32_t numObjOut = 0;
1724  uint32_t rangeIdx, dopplerIdx, peakVal;
1725  uint16_t *tempPtr;
1726  uint16_t kernel[9], detectedObjFlag;
1727  int32_t k, l;
1728  uint32_t startInd, stepInd, endInd;
1729 
1730  if ((groupInDopplerDirection == 1) && (groupInRangeDirection == 1))
1731  {
1732  /* Grouping both in Range and Doppler direction */
1733  startInd = 0;
1734  stepInd = 1;
1735  endInd = 8;
1736  }
1737  else if ((groupInDopplerDirection == 0) && (groupInRangeDirection == 1))
1738  {
1739  /* Grouping only in Range direction */
1740  startInd = 1;
1741  stepInd = 3;
1742  endInd = 7;
1743  }
1744  else if ((groupInDopplerDirection == 1) && (groupInRangeDirection == 0))
1745  {
1746  /* Grouping only in Doppler direction */
1747  startInd = 3;
1748  stepInd = 1;
1749  endInd = 5;
1750  }
1751  else
1752  {
1753  /* No grouping, copy all detected objects to the output matrix within specified min max range*/
1754  for(i = 0; i < MIN(numDetectedObjects, MMW_MAX_OBJ_OUT) ; i++)
1755  {
1756  if ((objRaw[i].rangeIdx <= maxRangeIdx) && ((objRaw[i].rangeIdx >= minRangeIdx)))
1757  {
1758  objOut[numObjOut].rangeIdx = objRaw[i].rangeIdx;
1759  objOut[numObjOut].dopplerIdx = DOPPLER_IDX_TO_SIGNED(objRaw[i].dopplerIdx, numDopplerBins);
1760  objOut[numObjOut].peakVal = objRaw[i].peakVal;
1761  numObjOut++;
1762  }
1763  }
1764  return numObjOut;
1765  }
1766 
1767  /* Start checking */
1768  for(i = 0; i < numDetectedObjects; i++)
1769  {
1770  detectedObjFlag = 0;
1771  rangeIdx = objRaw[i].rangeIdx;
1772  dopplerIdx = objRaw[i].dopplerIdx;
1773  peakVal = objRaw[i].peakVal;
1774  if((rangeIdx <= maxRangeIdx) && (rangeIdx >= minRangeIdx))
1775  {
1776  detectedObjFlag = 1;
1777 
1778  /* Fill local 3x3 kernel from detection matrix in L3*/
1779  tempPtr = detMatrix + (rangeIdx-1)*numDopplerBins;
1780  rowStart = 0;
1781  rowEnd = 2;
1782  if (rangeIdx == minRangeIdx)
1783  {
1784  tempPtr = detMatrix + (rangeIdx)*numDopplerBins;
1785  rowStart = 1;
1786  memset((void *) kernel, 0, 3 * sizeof(uint16_t));
1787  }
1788  else if (rangeIdx == maxRangeIdx)
1789  {
1790  rowEnd = 1;
1791  memset((void *) &kernel[6], 0, 3 * sizeof(uint16_t));
1792  }
1793 
1794  for (j = rowStart; j <= rowEnd; j++)
1795  {
1796  for (k = 0; k < 3; k++)
1797  {
1798  l = dopplerIdx + (k - 1);
1799  if(l < 0)
1800  {
1801  l += numDopplerBins;
1802  }
1803  else if(l >= numDopplerBins)
1804  {
1805  l -= numDopplerBins;
1806  }
1807  kernel[j*3+k] = tempPtr[l];
1808  }
1809  tempPtr += numDopplerBins;
1810  }
1811  /* Compare the detected object to its neighbors.
1812  * Detected object is at index 4*/
1813  for (k = startInd; k <= endInd; k += stepInd)
1814  {
1815  if(kernel[k] > kernel[4])
1816  {
1817  detectedObjFlag = 0;
1818  }
1819  }
1820  }
1821  if (detectedObjFlag == 1)
1822  {
1823  objOut[numObjOut].rangeIdx = rangeIdx;
1824  objOut[numObjOut].dopplerIdx = DOPPLER_IDX_TO_SIGNED(dopplerIdx, numDopplerBins);
1825  objOut[numObjOut].peakVal = peakVal;
1826  numObjOut++;
1827  }
1828  if (numObjOut >= MMW_MAX_OBJ_OUT)
1829  {
1830  break;
1831  }
1832 
1833  }
1834 
1835  return(numObjOut);
1836 }

1904  startInd = 3;
1905  stepInd = 1;
1906  endInd = 5;
1907  }
1908  else

1912  {

1916  objOut[numObjOut].dopplerIdx = DOPPLER_IDX_TO_SIGNED(objRaw[i].dopplerIdx, numDopplerBins);
1917  objOut[numObjOut].peakVal = objRaw[i].peakVal;
1918  numObjOut++;
1919  }
1920  }

1922  }
1923 
1924  /* Start checking */
1925  for(i = 0; i < numDetectedObjects ; i++)
1926  {
1927  detectedObjFlag = 0;
1928  rangeIdx = objRaw[i].rangeIdx;
1929  dopplerIdx = objRaw[i].dopplerIdx;
1930  peakVal = objRaw[i].peakVal;
1931 
1932  if((rangeIdx <= maxRangeIdx) && (rangeIdx >= minRangeIdx))
1933  {
1934  detectedObjFlag = 1;
1935  memset((void *) kernel, 0, 9*sizeof(uint16_t));
1936 
1937  /* Fill the middle column of the kernel */
1938  kernel[4] = peakVal;
1939 
1940  if (i > 0)
1941  {
1942  if ((objRaw[i-1].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx-1)) &&
1943  (objRaw[i-1].dopplerIdx == dopplerIdx))
1944  {
1945  kernel[1] = objRaw[i-1].peakVal;
1946  }
1947  }
1948 
1949  if (i < (numDetectedObjects - 1))
1950  {
1951  if ((objRaw[i+1].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx+1)) &&
1952  (objRaw[i+1].dopplerIdx == dopplerIdx))
1953  {
1954  kernel[7] = objRaw[i+1].peakVal;
1955  }
1956  }
1957 
1958  /* Fill the left column of the kernel */
1959  k = WRAP_UP_LIST_IDX(i-1);
1960  for (l = 0; l < numDetectedObjects; l++)
1961  {
1962  if (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx - 2))
1963  {
1964  break;
1965  }
1966  if ((objRaw[k].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx + 1)) &&
1967  (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx - 1)))
1968  {
1969  kernel[6] = objRaw[k].peakVal;
1970  }
1971  else if ((objRaw[k].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx)) &&
1972  (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx - 1)))
1973  {
1974  kernel[3] = objRaw[k].peakVal;
1975  }
1976  else if ((objRaw[k].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx - 1)) &&
1977  (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx - 1)))
1978  {
1979  kernel[0] = objRaw[k].peakVal;
1980  }
1981  k = WRAP_UP_LIST_IDX(k-1);
1982  }
1983 
1984  /* Fill the right column of the kernel */
1985  k = WRAP_DWN_LIST_IDX(i+1);
1986  for (l = 0; l < numDetectedObjects; l++)
1987  {
1988  if (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx + 2))
1989  {
1990  break;
1991  }
1992  if ((objRaw[k].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx - 1)) &&
1993  (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx + 1)))
1994  {
1995  kernel[2] = objRaw[k].peakVal;
1996  }
1997  else if ((objRaw[k].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx)) &&
1998  (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx + 1)))
1999  {
2000  kernel[5] = objRaw[k].peakVal;
2001  }
2002  else if ((objRaw[k].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx + 1)) &&
2003  (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx + 1)))
2004  {
2005  kernel[8] = objRaw[k].peakVal;
2006  }
2007  k = WRAP_DWN_LIST_IDX(k+1);
2008  }
2009 
2010  /* Compare the detected object to its neighbors.
2011  * Detected object is at index 4*/
2012  for (k = startInd; k <= endInd; k += stepInd)
2013  {
2014  if(kernel[k] > kernel[4])
2015  {
2016  detectedObjFlag = 0;
2017  }
2018  }
2019  }
2020  if(detectedObjFlag == 1)
2021  {
2022  objOut[numObjOut].rangeIdx = rangeIdx;
2023  objOut[numObjOut].dopplerIdx = DOPPLER_IDX_TO_SIGNED(dopplerIdx, numDopplerBins);
2024  objOut[numObjOut].peakVal = peakVal;
2025  numObjOut++;
2026  }
2027  if (numObjOut >= MMW_MAX_OBJ_OUT)
2028  {
2029  break;
2030  }
2031  }
2032 
2033  return(numObjOut);

2249 /*!*****************************************************************************************************************
2250  * \brief
2251  * Function Name : MmwDemo_DopplerCompensation
2252  *
2253  * \par
2254  * <b>Description</b> : Compensation of Doppler phase shift in the virtual antennas,
2255  * (corresponding to second Tx antenna chirps). Symbols
2256  * corresponding to virtual antennas, are rotated by half
2257  * of the Doppler phase shift measured by Doppler FFT.
2258  * The phase shift read from the table using half of the
2259  * object Doppler index value. If the Doppler index is
2260  * odd, an extra half of the bin phase shift is added.
2261  *
2262  * @param[in] dopplerIdx : Doppler index of the object
2263  *
2264  * @param[in] numDopplerBins : Number of Doppler bins
2265  *
2266  * @param[in] azimuthModCoefs: Table with cos/sin values SIN in even position, COS in odd position
2267  * exp(1j*2*pi*k/N) for k=0,...,N-1 where N is number of Doppler bins.
2268  *
2269  * @param[out] azimuthModCoefsHalfBin : exp(1j*2*pi* 0.5 /N)
2270  *
2271  * @param[in,out] azimuthIn :Pointer to antenna symbols to be Doppler compensated
2272  *
2273  * @param[in] numAnt : Number of antenna symbols to be Doppler compensated
2274  *
2275  * @return void
2276  *
2277  *******************************************************************************************************************
2278  */
2279 void MmwDemo_addDopplerCompensation(int32_t dopplerIdx,
2280  int32_t numDopplerBins,
2281  uint32_t *azimuthModCoefs,
2282  uint32_t *azimuthModCoefsHalfBin,
2283  int64_t *azimuthIn,
2284  uint32_t numAnt)
2285 {
2286  uint32_t expDoppComp;
2287  int32_t dopplerCompensationIdx = dopplerIdx;
2288  int64_t azimuthVal;
2289  int32_t Re, Im;
2290  uint32_t antIndx;
2291 
2292  if (numAnt == 0)
2293  {
2294  return;
2295  }
2296 
2297  /*Divide Doppler index by 2*/
2298  if (dopplerCompensationIdx >= numDopplerBins/2)
2299  {
2300  dopplerCompensationIdx -= (int32_t)numDopplerBins;
2301  }
2302  dopplerCompensationIdx = dopplerCompensationIdx / 2;
2303  if (dopplerCompensationIdx < 0)
2304  {
2305  dopplerCompensationIdx += (int32_t) numDopplerBins;
2306  }
2307  expDoppComp = azimuthModCoefs[dopplerCompensationIdx];
2308  /* Add half bin rotation if Doppler index was odd */
2309  if (dopplerIdx & 0x1)
2310  {
2311  expDoppComp = _cmpyr1(expDoppComp, *azimuthModCoefsHalfBin);
2312  }
2313 
2314  /* Rotate symbols */
2315  for (antIndx = 0; antIndx < numAnt; antIndx++)
2316  {
2317  azimuthVal = _amem8(&azimuthIn[antIndx]);
2318  Re = _ssub(_mpyhir(expDoppComp, _loll(azimuthVal) ),
2319  _mpylir(expDoppComp, _hill(azimuthVal)));
2320  Im = _sadd(_mpylir(expDoppComp, _loll(azimuthVal)),
2321  _mpyhir(expDoppComp, _hill(azimuthVal)));
2322  _amem8(&azimuthIn[antIndx]) = _itoll(Im, Re);
2323  }
2324 }

2474 #define MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_D (MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_C + 8.7)
2475

2479 #define MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_CB2 (2.0 * (MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_C - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B))
2480 #define MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_DB2 (2.0 * (MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_D - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B))
2481 #define MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_EB2 (2.0 * (MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_E - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B))
2482 
2483 #define MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_AB_SQ ((MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_A - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B) * (MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_A - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B))
2484 #define MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_CB_SQ ((MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_C - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B) * (MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_C - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B))
2485 #define MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_DB_SQ ((MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_D - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B) * (MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_D - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B))
2486 #define MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_EB_SQ ((MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_E - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B) * (MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_E - MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_B))
2487 
2488 #define MMWDEMO_TWO_PI_OVER_LAMBDA (2. * PI_ / MMWDEMO_XWR16XX_EVM_77GHZ_LAMBDA)
2489 
2490  int32_t i;
2491  float range;
2492  float rangeSq;
2493  cmplx32ReIm_t * azimuthOut0 = obj->azimuthOut;
2494  cmplx32ReIm_t * azimuthOut1 = &obj->azimuthOut[obj->numAngleBins];
2495  cmplx32ReIm_t azimuthOut1Corr;
2496  float corrReal;
2497  float corrImag;
2498  int32_t numAngleBins = obj->numAngleBins;
2499  float theta;
2500  float thetaInc = 2.0 / (float) obj->numAngleBins;
2501  float tx1, tx2, rx4, rx1;
2502  float psi;
2503 
2504  range = (obj->detObj2D[detIdx2].rangeIdx * obj->rangeResolution -
2505  obj->cliCommonCfg->compRxChanCfg.rangeBias) * 1000;
2506  rangeSq = range * range;
2507 
2508  corrReal = 1.0;
2509  corrImag = 0.0;
2510 
2511  for (i = 0; i < numAngleBins; i++)
2512  {
2513  if (i < numAngleBins/2)
2514  {
2515  theta = i * thetaInc;
2516  }
2517  else
2518  {
2519  theta = (i-numAngleBins) * thetaInc;
2520  }
2521  tx1 = sqrtsp(rangeSq + MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_CB_SQ - range * theta * MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_CB2);
2522  rx4 = sqrtsp(rangeSq + MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_DB_SQ - range * theta * MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_DB2);
2523  tx2 = sqrtsp(rangeSq + MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_AB_SQ - range * theta * MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_AB2);
2524  rx1 = sqrtsp(rangeSq + MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_EB_SQ - range * theta * MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_EB2);
2525 
2526  if (range > 0)
2527  {
2528  psi = MMWDEMO_TWO_PI_OVER_LAMBDA * ((tx2+rx1)-(rx4+tx1)) - PI_*theta;
2529  corrReal = cossp(psi);
2530  corrImag = sinsp(-psi);
2531  }
2532 
2533  azimuthOut1Corr.real = (int32_t) (azimuthOut1[i].real * corrReal - azimuthOut1[i].imag * corrImag);
2534  azimuthOut1Corr.imag = (int32_t) (azimuthOut1[i].imag * corrReal + azimuthOut1[i].real * corrImag);
2535  azimuthOut0[i].real = azimuthOut0[i].real + azimuthOut1Corr.real;
2536  azimuthOut0[i].imag = azimuthOut0[i].imag + azimuthOut1Corr.imag;
2537  }
2538 }

3847 void MmwDemo_genWindow(void *win,
3848  uint32_t windowDatumType,
3849  uint32_t winLen,
3850  uint32_t winGenLen,
3851  int32_t oneQformat,
3852  uint32_t winType)
3853 {
3854  uint32_t winIndx;
3855  int32_t winVal;
3856  int16_t * win16 = (int16_t *) win;
3857  int32_t * win32 = (int32_t *) win;
3858 
3859  float eR = 1.;
3860  float eI = 0.;
3861  float e2R = 1.;
3862  float e2I = 0.;
3863  float ephyR, ephyI;
3864  float e2phyR, e2phyI;
3865  float tmpR;
3866 
3867  float phi = 2 * PI_ / ((float) winLen - 1);
3868 
3869 
3870  ephyR = cossp(phi);
3871  ephyI = sinsp(phi);
3872 
3873  e2phyR = ephyR * ephyR - ephyI * ephyI;
3874  e2phyI = 2 * ephyR * ephyI;
3875 
3876 
3877  if(winType == MMW_WIN_BLACKMAN)
3878  {
3879  //Blackman window
3880  float a0 = 0.42;
3881  float a1 = 0.5;
3882  float a2 = 0.08;
3883  for(winIndx = 0; winIndx < winGenLen; winIndx++)
3884  {
3885  winVal = (int32_t) ((oneQformat * (a0 - a1*eR + a2*e2R)) + 0.5);
3886  if(winVal >= oneQformat)
3887  {
3888  winVal = oneQformat - 1;
3889  }
3890  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT16)
3891  {
3892  win16[winIndx] = (int16_t) winVal;
3893  }
3894  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT32)
3895  {
3896  win32[winIndx] = (int32_t) winVal;
3897  }
3898  tmpR = eR;
3899  eR = eR * ephyR - eI * ephyI;
3900  eI = tmpR * ephyI + eI * ephyR;
3901 
3902  tmpR = e2R;
3903  e2R = e2R * e2phyR - e2I * e2phyI;
3904  e2I = tmpR * e2phyI + e2I * e2phyR;
3905  }
3906  }
3907  else if (winType == MMW_WIN_HANNING)
3908  {
3909  //Hanning window
3910  for(winIndx = 0; winIndx < winGenLen; winIndx++)
3911  {
3912  winVal = (int32_t) ((oneQformat * 0.5* (1 - eR)) + 0.5);
3913  if(winVal >= oneQformat)
3914  {
3915  winVal = oneQformat - 1;
3916  }
3917  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT16)
3918  {
3919  win16[winIndx] = (int16_t) winVal;
3920  }
3921  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT32)
3922  {
3923  win32[winIndx] = (int32_t) winVal;
3924  }
3925  tmpR = eR;
3926  eR = eR*ephyR - eI*ephyI;
3927  eI = tmpR*ephyI + eI*ephyR;
3928  }
3929  }
3930  else if (winType == MMW_WIN_RECT)
3931  {
3932  //Rectangular window
3933  for(winIndx = 0; winIndx < winGenLen; winIndx++)
3934  {
3935  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT16)
3936  {
3937  win16[winIndx] = (int16_t) (oneQformat-1);
3938  }
3939  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT32)
3940  {
3941  win32[winIndx] = (int32_t) (oneQformat-1);
3942  }
3943  }
3944  }
3945 }
